article.headline: IUPUI 91, UMKC 83
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Odell Bradley scored a career-high 32 points to lead IUPUI to a 91-83 victory over Missouri-Kansas City Thursday at Hale Arena. The Jaguars (11-7, 4-2 Mid-Continent Conference) broke a two-game losing streak, while the Kangaroos (9-8, 4-2) had a five-game winning streak snapped. UMKC, which never led, cut the lead to 64-63 on a bucket by freshman Blake Crawford with 7 minutes left in the game. IUPUI then connected on 17 straight free throws before Bradley missed one with 21 seconds left to keep the lead. Bradley, who also had a game-high nine rebounds, was 10-of-18 from the field and 12-of-14 from the free-throw line. Akeem Clark added 21 points, and Brandon Cole had 19 for the Jaguars. IUPUI was 23-of-26 from the free-throw line and 10-of-19 from the 3-point range. Michael Watson had 27 points for UMKC. He was one of five Kangaroos who scored in double figures; Mike English had 14 points, Brandon Temple and Corey Starks had 12 each, and Brandon Lipsey had 11.
